contentrichtext.text: {{TOCright}} '''[[Orléans]]''' is a city in north-central France, about 100 km south-west of Paris. '''Orleans''' may also refer to: ==Places== In '''Brazil''': *[[Orleans, Santa Catarina]] In '''Canada''': *[[Île d'Orléans]], an island in the St. Lawrence River near Québec city *[[Orleans, Ontario]], a community which became part of the city of Ottawa in 2001 In the '''United States''': *[[Orleans, California]] *Orleans, former name of [[Orleans Flat, California]] *[[Orleans, Indiana]] *[[Orleans, Iowa]] *[[Orleans, Massachusetts]] *[[Orleans, Nebraska]] *[[Orleans, New York]] *[[Orleans, Vermont]] *[[New Orleans, Louisiana]] {{seealso|Orleans County (disambiguation)|Orleans Township (disambiguation)}} ==Other uses== *[[House of Orléans]], French royal family **[[Charlotte Orléans]], a fictional character in a royal family possibly inspired by this *[[Orleans (band)]], a 1970s rock band *[[Orleans (TV series)|''Orleans'' (TV series)]], a 1997 CBS television series *[[The Orleans Hotel and Casino]], a hotel and casino in Las Vegas, Nevada *[[US Orléans]], a French football club *[[Orléans (grape)]], a white grape variety *[[Canal d'Orléans]], a canal in France. ==See also== *[[Duke of Orléans]] {{disambig}} [[Category:Place name disambiguation pages]]
